# Comparative Law System

This is LexMastery's differentiator.

It enables cross-jurisdiction legal understanding.

---

# Product Vision

Comparative Law must:

- compare legal systems across jurisdictions
- explain differences clearly
- support exam preparation
- simplify complex legal contrasts
- provide AI-driven legal mapping

---

# Core Concept

Users must be able to:

- compare laws between countries
- understand procedural differences
- analyze legal frameworks side-by-side

---

# Architecture

Presentation Layer

↓

ComparativeLawController (Riverpod)

↓

ComparativeLawState

↓

ComparativeLawRepository

↓

AI Legal Comparison Engine

---

# State Management

ComparativeLawState includes:

- loading
- comparing
- resultReady
- error

Core Data:

- jurisdictionA
- jurisdictionB
- comparisonTopics
- structuredDifferences
- AIInsights

---

# Comparison Dimensions

- Constitutional law
- Criminal law
- Civil procedure
- Contract law
- Evidence rules
- Court hierarchy
- Legal education systems

---

# AI Integration

AI must:

- generate structured comparisons
- simplify legal complexity
- highlight exam-relevant differences
- avoid hallucinated legal claims

---

# Output Format

Comparisons must include:

- side-by-side structure
- summary section
- key differences
- exam relevance notes

---

# Navigation Rules

Comparative Law connects to:

- Courses
- AI Tutor
- Search System
- Notes

---

# Offline Behaviour

- cached comparisons available
- AI comparison disabled offline
- static comparison view allowed

---

# API Contracts

POST /compare/law

GET /compare/history

GET /compare/jurisdictions

---

# Analytics Events

comparison_started

comparison_completed

comparison_saved

comparison_shared

---

# UX Rules

- comparisons must be structured
- avoid long unstructured AI text
- highlight key differences visually

---

# UI Composition Rules

Must include:

- dual-panel layout
- highlight differences
- summary panel
- AI explanation toggle

---

# Error Handling

- fallback to cached comparisons
- retry AI comparison safely

---

# Performance

- comparison generation <2s target
- UI must render partial results progressively

---

# Accessibility

Must support:

- screen reader structured comparison navigation
- clear headings per jurisdiction

---

# Testing Requirements

